I'm using cocos2d-x-3.13.1

While working with "*.9.png" images I have just noticed some inconsistency in the code that I can't understand. 

`Scale9Sprite::createSlicedSprites()` function has this code:

`auto originalSize = CC_SIZE_POINTS_TO_PIXELS(_originalSize);
if (_isPatch9)
{
    originalSize = Size(originalSize.width - 2, originalSize.height-2);
}`

Here we are decreasing size for 2 pixels in width and height.

And there are another part of code where we also apply magic number two (2) but on size variable fields that not in pixel coordinates but on design resolution coordinates, see `Scale9Sprite::updateWithSprite`:

`if(this->_isPatch9)
  {
     size.width = size.width - 2;
     size.height = size.height - 2;
  }
  this->setContentSize(size);
`
I assume that this number has here same meaning as in the first case so probably it must be converted to design resolution here before subtracting from size.

